The Oyo State Police Command has warned members of the public against the use of fireworks and holding of unauthorised street carnivals during the Yuletide. The state Commissioner of Police, Shina Olukolu, gave the warning on Friday while addressing newsmen on the efforts being put together by the command to combat crime, particularly during the festive period. Olukolu warned criminals to steer off the state, saying the long arm of the law would surely catch up with them. The commissioner of police said the state would not be a safe haven for criminals to carry out their evil acts. “There will be intense and aggressive routine police patrols and stop-and-search operations by men in vehicles, both within and outside Ibadan metropolis. “I assure the members of the public of the police preparedness to protect lives and property before, during and after the Yuletide period,” he said. Olukolu enjoined residents of the state to continue to partner with the police by providing useful, timely and credible information. He also implored the residents to go about their lawful businesses without any fear of molestation. Vanguard News Nigeria. IBADAN—THE Oyo State Police Command has arrested no fewer than 29 suspects in connection with pockets of skirmishes within the National Union of Road Transport Workers, NURTW, in Oyo State.Police arrest 29 over NURTW crisis in Ibadan June 4, 2019 In "News" Mr Shina Olukolu, the Commissioner of Police in Oyo, has urged police officers in the command to undertake their duties with the fear of God. Olukolu made the call on Friday evening during a dinner and award presentation ceremony held at the state police headquarters, Eleyele, Ibadan. He said that… December 14, 2019 In "News" The Oyo State Police Command on Wednesday paraded 18 suspects in connection with alleged armed robbery, impersonation, possession of human skull and hijacking a tanker loaded with Premium Motor Spirit (PMS). March 6, 2019 In "Crime Alert"